James Frey is the protagonist and narrator. James is a23-year-old man with a serious drug and alcohol problem. When the book opens, James is a physical and mental wreck, forced to enter the worldâ€™s most successful drug and alcohol clinic. During his stay, he battles his personal demons, makes an unusual group of friends, and falls in love with a drug-addicted former prostitute named Lilly. He adopts a philosophy of self-reliance and rejects the traditional forms of treatment (as exemplified in the Twelve Steps of Alcoholics Anonymous). Unlike many of the people he meets in the clinic, James emerges sober and takes control of his life.Read anin-depth analysis of James Frey.